  "text": "The gRPC health check protocol implementation in envoyproxy/envoy is located in the extensions/health_checkers/grpc module. The core implementation files are:\n\n1. **source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h**: Header file defining the GrpcHealthCheckerFactory (line 30), GrpcHealthCheckerImpl class (line 47), and the nested GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession class (line 54). The GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession contains a std::unique_ptr<grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse> member (line 121) that stores the health check response.\n\n2. **source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc**: Implementation file containing:\n   - GrpcHealthCheckerFactory::createCustomHealthChecker (line 45): Factory method that creates ProdGrpcHealthCheckerImpl instances\n   - GrpcHealthCheckerImpl constructor (line 55): Initializes by looking up the gRPC service method \"grpc.health.v1.Health.Check\" (line 63-64)\n   - GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::onInterval (line 186): Sends the health check request by creating a grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckRequest (line 233) and encoding it using Grpc::Common::serializeToGrpcFrame\n   - GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::decodeData (line 130): Parses the incoming gRPC response frames and deserializes the grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse (line 151)\n   - GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::decodeTrailers (line 164): Handles gRPC status in trailers\n   - GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::isHealthCheckSucceeded (line 300): Determines health based on gRPC status being OK and the response status being grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::SERVING (line 307)\n   - GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::logHealthCheckStatus (line 365): Maps health check response status values including SERVING, NOT_SERVING, UNKNOWN, and SERVICE_UNKNOWN (lines 371-387)\n\n3. **source/common/grpc/common.h & common.cc**: Provides gRPC utility functions:\n   - Common::serializeToGrpcFrame (line 168 in cc file): Serializes protobuf messages into gRPC frame format with the 5-byte header (flags + length)\n   - Common::getGrpcStatus (line 101 in cc file): Extracts gRPC status from headers/trailers\n   - Common::isGrpcResponseHeaders (line 83 in cc file): Validates gRPC response headers\n\n4. **api/envoy/config/core/v3/health_check.proto**: Defines the GrpcHealthCheck message (line 205) that configures gRPC health checking with service_name and authority fields (lines 209-221)\n\nThe implementation follows the gRPC Health Checking Protocol specification by:\n- Using the grpc.health.v1.Health.Check unary RPC method\n- Sending HealthCheckRequest messages with optional service_name parameter\n- Receiving HealthCheckResponse messages and checking the status field\n- Mapping response status values (SERVING=healthy, NOT_SERVING/UNKNOWN/SERVICE_UNKNOWN=unhealthy)\n- Properly handling gRPC status codes and HTTP/2 trailers for error conditions"
}

